<item>
            <title>[OAK-1781] Too many branch commits on document node store</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-1781</link>
                <project id="12313221" key="OAK">Jackrabbit Oak</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The fix for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-1056&quot; title=&quot;Transient changes contributed by commit hooks are kept in memory&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;OAK-1056&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;OAK-1056&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; introduced a regression which causes preliminary creation of the persisted branch instead of keeping changes in memory up to a certain size. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The problem is that transient changes are &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/jackrabbit-oak/blob/1e4eb5f15d36922c8e6eaa8ff1316e5f512f4352/oak-core/src/main/java/org/apache/jackrabbit/oak/plugins/document/DocumentRootBuilder.java#L107&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;purged&lt;/a&gt; with every call to &lt;tt&gt;NodeBuilder.getNodeState&lt;/tt&gt;. That purge is what ultimately leads to the persisted branch being created. &lt;/p&gt;
</description>
